leads.headline: getByPath and setByPath return any
leads.analysis:
The getByPath and setByPath functions both use type assertions to any.
This means that the type checker will not be able to verify that the path is valid or that the value being set is of the correct type.
This could lead to runtime errors that would not be caught by the type checker.
